**Implementing Fade-In Animation**

I'm currently focused on implementing a fade-in animation for the project cards. My initial approach leverages the Intersection Observer API for viewport detection, combined with React's `useEffect`, and `useRef` hooks to manage the animation lifecycle within the React component. I'm aiming for a clean and efficient implementation.


**Refining Visibility Logic**

I'm now diving into the `useIntersectionObserver` hook, the heart of this fade-in functionality. It will handle element visibility tracking. The focus is to make it reusable and efficient; I'm wrapping the Intersection Observer logic. The hook's output will be a boolean indicating viewport visibility. I will ensure React's component re-renders accordingly.


**Defining the ProjectCard Implementation**

I'm now outlining the steps to integrate the fade-in into the `ProjectCard` component. I need a ref for the root element and will use the `useIntersectionObserver` hook to track visibility. Based on that visibility state, I will conditionally add CSS classes for the animation. My plan is to start with initial classes like `opacity-0 translate-y-4` and then switch to `opacity-100 translate-y-0` on visibility, using Tailwind CSS's transition utilities to handle the animation itself.


**Refining Implementation Strategy**

I'm now deciding where to place the `useIntersectionObserver` logic. While initially considering a separate hook file or integrating it directly into `App.tsx`, I've settled on embedding the visibility handling within the `ProjectCard` component itself, to enhance encapsulation and reduce complexity. I am exploring modifications to `ProjectCard` to manage its own animation.

```typescript
// In App.tsx

import React, { useRef, useState, useEffect } from 'react'; // Add useRef, useState, useEffect
// ... other imports

// ...

interface ProjectCardProps {
    date: string;
    title: string;
    description: string[];
    index: number; // Add index for staggered animation delay
}

const ProjectCard: React.FC<ProjectCardProps> = ({ date, title, description, index }) => {
    const cardRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
    const [isVisible, setIsVisible] = useState(false);

    useEffect(() => {
        const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
            (entries) => {
                entries.forEach(entry => {
                    if (entry.isIntersecting) {
                        setIsVisible(true);
                        observer.unobserve(cardRef.current!); // Stop observing once visible
                    }
                });
            },
            {
                root: null, // Use the viewport
                rootMargin: '0px',
                threshold: 0.2, // Trigger when 20% of the card is visible
            }
        );

        if (cardRef.current) {
            observer.observe(cardRef.current);
        }

        return () => {
            if (cardRef.current) {
                observer.unobserve(cardRef.current);
            }
        };
    }, []);

    const animationDelay = `${index * 0.1}s`; // Stagger animation

    return (
        <div
            ref={cardRef}
            className={`
                relative flex flex-col justify-between p-6 bg-white shadow-md rounded-md
                ${isVisible ? 'opacity-100 translate-y-0' : 'opacity-0 translate-y-4'}
                transition-opacity duration-700 ease-in-out
                ${isVisible ? 'duration-1000' : ''}
                `}
            style={{ animationDelay }}
        >
            {/* Content  */}
        </div>
    );
};
```

