payload.text:
This error in React means:

You are trying to render a JavaScript object inside JSX instead of valid content like a string, number, or JSX element.

The part that says:

object with keys {$$typeof, type, key, ref, props}


usually means you accidentally rendered a React element object incorrectly.

✅ Quick Fixed Solutions
1️⃣ Check for this mistake

❌ Wrong:

{MyComponent}


✅ Correct:

<MyComponent />

2️⃣ Do NOT render plain objects

❌ Wrong:

const user = { name: "Srujan" };
return <div>{user}</div>;


✅ Correct:

return <div>{user.name}</div>;

3️⃣ Fix map() return issues

❌ Wrong:

users.map(user => {
  <div>{user.name}</div>
});


✅ Correct:

users.map(user => (
  <div key={user.id}>{user.name}</div>
));

4️⃣ Do not wrap JSX inside extra curly braces

❌ Wrong:

<div>{{ component }}</div>


✅ Correct:

<div>{component}</div>

5️⃣ Check for this common mistake

If you see something like:

return {
  <div>Hello</div>
}


That is wrong. Remove the {}:

return (
  <div>Hello</div>
);

🔎 Best Way to Debug

Run your app in development mode:

npm start


or

npm run dev


It will show the exact line number causing the error.

Search your project for:

{something} inside JSX

return {

{Component}

